1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - This paper primarily focuses on analyzing the properties of the overlay generated by BitTorrent, which is a peer-to-peer file sharing protocol. The analysis involves studying the connectivity and efficiency of the overlay, which are key aspects of networking and internet architecture. 

2. cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing) - BitTorrent is a distributed computing system that relies on peers to share files. The paper analyzes the properties of the overlay generated by BitTorrent, which is a key component of the system. The analysis involves studying the efficiency and robustness of the overlay, which are important aspects of distributed computing. 

3. cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) - BitTorrent is a peer-to-peer file sharing protocol that relies on social networks to facilitate file sharing. The paper analyzes the properties of the overlay generated by BitTorrent, which is a key component of the social network. The analysis involves studying the connectivity and efficiency of the overlay, which are important aspects of social networks. 

4. cs.PF (Performance) - The paper analyzes the properties of the overlay generated by BitTorrent, with a focus on its efficiency and robustness.
